properties.otherAdvice:
Road closures and special event clearways will be in effect on Saturday 29 and Sunday 30 October while filming takes place in the Sydney CBD.

  • From 6am to 7pm each day sections of Bent St, Bligh St, Elizabeth St, Hunter St, King St, Phillip Ln and Phillip St will be closed.

The cycleway on King St between Elizabeth St and Phillip St will also be closed from 6am to 7pm each day.

Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on Saturday and Sunday from 4am to 7pm each day on sections of Bathurst St, Bent St, Bligh St, Bridge St, Castlereagh St, Clarence St, College St, Elizabeth St, Hunter St, King St, Macquarie St, Market St, Pitt St, Phillip St and St James Rd.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, even for local residents or TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in signposted clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed call 132 701 to find its new location.
